cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.AL, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with scheduling packets on directed line networks, which is a networking problem. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents an algorithmic solution to the packet scheduling problem. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The problem of packet scheduling on a network can be seen as a distributed computing problem. 
4. cs.AL (Algorithms) - The paper presents a new algorithm for the packet scheduling problem. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the problem of delivering packets to their destination without violating capacity constraints, which is related to information theory.
